  "text": "In the case of the sav Zfh1 DamID peak, the flanking GATC sites are separated by 1063bp. This region contains a short motif with high similarity (10bp of 12bp identical) to the repressive Zfh1 homeodomain binding site within the eve mesodermal enhancer [CITATION_1] , that had in turn been recognized due to its similarity to the conserved RCSI homeodomain binding motif used for cloning zfh1 . ( Figure 6A ). Similar, putative Zfh1 homeodomain binding sites corresponding to the degenerate sequence CTAATYRRNTT used to identify the eve RCSI-like motif [CITATION_2] were indeed significantly enriched in Zfh1 DamID peaks from both S2 cells (PWMenrich raw score 1.377; p=8.06 E-11) and CySCs (raw score 1.421; p=1.377 E-07) (Stojnic, R. and Diez, D. (2015) . PWMEnrich, R package 4.6.0).",
